---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { organizationSchema, daveDelaneyPersonSchema } from '../data/schema.js';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Communication Expert, Leadership Coach, Keynote Speaker in Nashville and beyond. It's Futureforth. - Futureforth"
  description="Looking for keynote speakers in Nashville? Are you seeking a communication expert who brings humor, heart, and wisdom to his work? Futureforth presents former Google Speaker, Dave Delaney, an award-winning communication consultant, coach, and expert in networking, connection, community, and communication skills."
  path="/about"
  image="/images/about-dave.jpg"
  jsonLd={[organizationSchema, daveDelaneyPersonSchema]}
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow" style="color: var(--color-accent);">Our Story</p>
      <h1>About Futureforth</h1>
      <p class="lede" style="color:#dbe3ee;">
        At Futureforth, we believe that clear communication and professional development aren't just
        skills &mdash; they're game-changers. Whether you're an executive feeling stuck, a founder
        figuring out your next move, a freelancer ready to grow, or a mid-career professional overwhelmed
        and unclear, you're not alone.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <p>Futureforth is here to help you gain <strong>clarity, confidence, and momentum</strong>.</p>
      <h2>What We Do</h2>
      <p>Futureforth is a coaching and communication consultancy that supports those who are ready to take the next step, even if they're not yet sure what that step is.</p>
      <p>We offer:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>1:1 coaching</strong> to help you clarify your direction and communicate it powerfully</li>
        <li><strong>Keynote presentations and workshops</strong> for conferences and organizations that want to elevate connection, creativity, and leadership</li>
        <li><strong>Fractional and contract engagements</strong> to transform your company's communication &mdash; internally and externally</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Our approach is built on action, not fluff. You'll walk away with new strategies, renewed energy,
        and the confidence to speak up, stand out, and reach the success you've been striving for.
        <a href="/contact">Schedule a quick call to learn more</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--alt" id="dave">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="hero__grid hero__grid--split">
        <div>
          <img src="/images/about-dave.jpg" alt="Dave Delaney, communication expert, leadership coach, and keynote speaker" width="640" height="640" loading="lazy" style="border-radius: var(--radius-lg); box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);" />
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Who's Behind Futureforth?</p>
          <h2>About Dave Delaney</h2>
          <p>
            <strong>Dave Delaney</strong>, founder of Futureforth, is a communication strategist, coach,
            and acclaimed keynote speaker. Delaney helps professionals and teams enhance their
            connection, leadership, and growth. Known for his blend of humor, heart, experience, and
            actionable insights, Dave teaches communication and leadership through keynote presentations,
            workshops, coaching, and as a fractional strategic communication director.
          </p>
          <p>
            With an extensive background in marketing, digital content creation, technology, performance,
            networking, and even improv comedy, Dave is recognized for his ability to engage audiences,
            teams, and individuals and drive real results. Delaney is a recognized leader, published
            author of <a href="/new-business-networking">New Business Networking</a>, and the host and
            producer of the ADHD Wise Squirrels podcast.
          </p>
          <p>
            A trusted voice on communication and connection, Dave has worked with top organizations like
            Google, LinkedIn, FedEx, and UPS. His expertise has been featured in USA Today, Forbes,
            Entrepreneur, BBC, CBC, and multiple books.
          </p>
          <p>
            If you're looking for a communication expert to <strong>enlighten</strong>,
            <strong>empower</strong>, and <strong>entertain</strong> your audience or team while
            delivering practical takeaways, they don't call him the <em>nice</em> guy for nothing.
            <a href="/contact">Check Dave's availability</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <details style="margin-top: var(--space-xl);">
        <summary style="cursor: pointer; font-weight: 700; font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: var(--step-1);">More about Dave&hellip;</summary>
        <div style="margin-top: var(--space-sm); max-width: 60ch;">
          <p>
            Dave Delaney is a natural communicator whose real strength lies in how easily he builds trust
            with others. People consistently describe him as someone who listens well, tells meaningful
            stories, and makes genuine connections with just about anyone &mdash; regardless of their
            background or status.
          </p>
          <p>
            Colleagues and friends often mention that Dave brings energy, warmth, and humor into every
            interaction. He's known for being generous with his time and ideas, always offering help
            without expecting anything in return.
          </p>
          <p>
            His ability to share enthusiasm, connect across differences, and communicate clearly &mdash;
            both in person and online &mdash; comes up again and again. At the core, Dave's
            &ldquo;superpower&rdquo; is a mix of authenticity, curiosity, and kindness that helps others
            feel more confident, connected, and understood.
          </p>
          <p>
            In his work, Dave uses these qualities to teach communication in a way that's practical and
            human. His keynotes and workshops are known for being engaging and full of real-life
            takeaways &mdash; whether he's talking about team communication, retention, neurodiversity,
            or leadership.
          </p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section text-center">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Why &ldquo;Futureforth&rdquo;?</h2>
      <p class="lede" style="margin-inline: auto;">
        Because that's what we're doing here &mdash; looking ahead, getting unstuck, and moving forward
        with purpose. In the wise words of Joey Ramone, with his clenched fist held proudly in the air,
        &ldquo;Hey ho, let's go!&rdquo;
      </p>
      <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Contact Us</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
